The paper proposes a new algorithm for binary classification from crowdsourced data, which falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The algorithm also involves probabilistic methods and Bayesian inference, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and statistical inference (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of online and offline settings, which suggests that it may fall under the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computer vision (cs.CV).
